Their wings spread like an artful love,

The mountains, majestic and grand,
A testament to nature's might,
Their peaks soaring into the sky,
A symbol of unyielding strength and enduring height.

A work of art that will never fade or wane,
A treasure trove of wonder and delight,
A beauty that transcends all forms of light.
